56.0	Isaac_Bashevis_Singer	Isaac Bashevis Singer	Isaac Bashevis Singer (Yiddish: ; November 21, 1902 (see notes below) â€“ July 24, 1991) was a Polish Jewish American author best known for his short stories. He was a leading figure in the Yiddish literary movement and won the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1978. He won two U.S. National Book Awards, one in Children's Literature for his memoir A Day Of Pleasure: Stories of a Boy Growing Up in Warsaw and one in Fiction for his collection A Crown of Feathers and Other Stories.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Isaac_Bashevis_Singer_crop.jpg/250px-Isaac_Bashevis_Singer_crop.jpg
